Description: Said to bestow talent in the arts to the one who displays it. Any reports of it crafting shoes by night are likely exaggerated.

Description: Said to bless the one who displays it with wisdom. Any reports of its eyes moving on their own accord are greatly exaggerated. Probably.

Description:
A delightful set of bite-sized morsels of baked chocolate fashioned to resemble spriggans. So delicious you're certain to sprigg for more!

※Cannot be retrieved once used.
※Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%

Plural: servings of authentic Costa del Hielo
Description:
A delicious chilled dessert created by the confectioner Nekeke, this icy treat is both refreshing and easy on the waistline, as it largely consists of frozen water. Guaranteed to be exactly as hydrating as it has always been.

※Cannot be retrieved once used.
※Can be used up to 10 times.

  Gear Durability Bonus: +3

Description:
Sweet millioncorn on the cob, basted with authentic Hingan soy sauce and broiled over an open flame. So succulently delicious, you won't want to miss a kernel.

※Cannot be retrieved once used.
※Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)
Name: Authentic Grilled Corn

Description: A stone bridge tastefully hemmed with tendrils of creeping ivy.

Description: Curious what lies beyond the garden wall? The garden gate is here to help.

Description: An egg-themed chocobo harness created in celebration of Hatching-tide. The authentic hat is rumored to have highly advanced egg-detection functionalities.
Name: Authentic Egg Barding

Description: A gaudy suit of chocobo armor designed for use during Valentione's Day celebrations. While some─including your steed─may question your fashion sense, the authenticity of your passion will be indisputable to all.
Name: Authentic Paramour Barding

Description: A frill-rimmed umbrella perfect for any weather except rain. Use to unlock a white lace parasol.
Name: White Lace Parasol

Description: A white umbrella printed with a charming pattern of blue flowers, moogles, chocobos, and more. Use to unlock a blue blossom parasol.
Name: Blue Blossom Parasol

Description: These tinted lenses will place you at the forefront of trendiness─so long as you avoid bumping into anything while wearing them. Use to unlock a pair of false shaded spectacles.
Name: False Shaded Spectacles

Description:
Wear these for a classic look of intelligence.*
* Glasses have no effect on actual intelligence. Generous bouts of silence may be advised. Use to unlock a pair of false classic spectacles.
Name: False Classic Spectacles

Description: Synthetic material invented and woven by the Loporrits. The texture is exhilaratingly different on either side.
Name: Exciting Fiber

Description: Stone pulled from the bottom of the Sirensong Sea.
Name: Deep-sea Marble

Description: A myriad assortment of seeds harvested from natural flotsam.
Name: Driftseeds

Description: This highly collectable feather appears to be larger and more beautiful than that of any documented fauna.
Name: Resplendent Feather

Description: A feather the color of a deep night sky yearning for dawn.
Name: Blue Feather

Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of appointed attire.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.
Name: Appointed Attire Coffer

Description: A fibrous frond from a palm tree native to the Cieldalaes.
Name: Island Palm Leaf

Description: A variety of apple selectively bred to not only survive, but flourish in the hot and humid climes of the southern isles.
Name: Island Apple

Description: An extra rest cycle is recommended for any mammets found using this small branch to charge down nearby windmills.
Name: Island Branch

Description: This stone has not gone unturned. Now for the rest...
Name: Island Stone

Description: A clam native to the Rhotano Sea, scooped from island sands despite its best efforts.
Name: Island Clam

Description: One can convert this seaweed into black salt by burning it to a crisp, providing additional salt variety when the entirety of the ocean simply will not suffice.
Name: Island Laver

Description: A fragment of coral native to the Rhotano Sea, commonly found along the coasts of isles in the Cieldalaes.
Name: Island Coral

Description: This common grass found growing throughout the Cieldalaes can be used as an ingredient in delicious salads and markedly less delicious potions.
Name: Islewort

Description: A sack of rough and coarse sand gathered from an isle in the Cieldalaes. Some say it has a mind of its own, with the charming proclivity to get anywhere─and everywhere─it possibly can.
Name: Island Sand

Description: A freshly cut log of timber that mammets have helpfully identified as “from a tree.”
Name: Island Log

Description: A fragrant, freshly cut log of timber from a palm tree native to the Cieldalaes.
Name: Island Palm Log

Description: Highly elastic vine harvested on an isle in the Cieldalaes.
Name: Island Vine

Description: A sweet, sticky substance harvested from trees in the Cieldalaes.
Name: Island Sap

Description: A sizable chunk of metallic ore mined in the Cieldalaes.
Name: Island Copper Ore

Description: This sedimentary rock does not, in fact, taste of refreshing lime. Not that you would know.
Name: Island Limestone

Description: This red-hued salt is prized by islekeeps for its role in the creation of homemade frozen treats and myriad practical uses. By contrast─and for reasons unknown to the locals─certain Cieldalaes tourists insist upon licking it directly.
Name: Island Rock Salt

Description: The sturdy and stout stalk of this native flora is rich in sugar, making it far superior to other island plants. Especially that salad one.
Name: Island Sugarcane

Description: The fluffy flower of a cotton plant, buffeted by Rhotano breezes no more.
Name: Island Cotton Boll

Description: The stalk of this sun-kissed plant contains fibers used for weaving─and only weaving, in case anyone asks.
Name: Island Hemp

Description: Natural clay of the Cieldalaes variety, which is to say, “excessively and perennially damp.”
Name: Island Clay

Description: This sand sourced from Cieldalaes waters contains a high concentration of tiny grains of tin.
Name: Island Tinsand

Description: A sizable chunk of iron-imbued ore mined in the Cieldalaes.
Name: Island Iron Ore

Description: What distinguishes this translucent mass of unpolished quartz from others is the novelty of its source in the Cieldalaes...so very little, all told.
Name: Island Quartz

Description: Attempting to say the name of this pale igneous rock three times in a row without severing one's tongue is a tried and true islekeep's pastime.
Name: Island Leucogranite

Description: Much like any wavekin, the islefish loves a nice body of water on a hot day, and also all other days.
Name: Islefish

Description: A traveling culinarian once claimed that such squid offer a uniquely “tropical” flavor, but failed to mention how it was seasoned before her passing, thus accidentally spawning a culinary controversy that continues to this day. Let this be a warning.
Name: Island Squid

Description: Innocuous though it may seem, this species of jellyfish makes a habit of swarming island coasts during the summer season, and has not proven particularly reticent to sting those who risk a dip in the water.
Name: Island Jellyfish

Description: A rare species of alyssum found only in the Cieldalaes. Though it possesses a sweet honey fragrance, the flavor leaves much to be desired.
Name: Island Alyssum

Description: This dark red garnet is hard enough to sharpen a dagger─a strange priority to have, come to think of it, but here we are.
Name: Raw Island Garnet

Description:
A freshly cut log of timber from a spruce native to the Cieldalaes.

...That wasn't so hard, now was it, mammets?
Name: Island Spruce Log

Description: The thalassocracy advises its islekeeps to seek shade and a tall glass of water immediately should they find themselves muttering, “There must be a nailhead out there somewhere”─a suspected early symptom of islestroke.
Name: Island Hammerhead

Description: A sizable chunk of shining ore mined in the Cieldalaes.
Name: Island Silver Ore

Description:
A bag chock-full of island popoto pieces that can be used to grow more popotoes, perpetuating an infinite popoto cycle that likely predates the advent of agriculture.

[Growth Period: Two days]
Name: Island Popoto Set

Description:
A bag containing countless cabbage seeds, to be planted by those who enjoy their greens pale and tasting of flatulence.

[Growth Period: Two days]
Name: Island Cabbage Seeds

Description:
A bag plump with isleberry seeds. Plant them, grow them, weather an intense battle with the local birds, eat them.

[Growth Period: Two days]
Name: Isleberry Seeds

Description:
One might say this is a bag full of pump's kin. Or one might not.

[Growth Period: Two days]
Name: Island Pumpkin Seeds

Description:
A bag of onion cuttings. They can be planted as is, and will quickly mature into large onion bulbs─unless the gardening mammets get hungry.

[Growth Period: Two days]
Name: Island Onion Set

Description:
Though one may be unable to facilitate peace between those who call them toe-may-toes versus toe-mah-toes ere these seeds ripen, there is certainly time to cultivate a robust sunburn in solidarity.

[Growth Period: Two days]
Name: Island Tomato Seeds

Description:
You will get wheat.

[Growth Period: Two days]
Name: Island Wheat Seeds

Description:
There was once a La Noscean farmer who insisted the growth of this crop was powered by puns. He has since been shipped off to a sanctuary, where he may do the world no more harm. 

[Growth Period: Two days]
Name: Island Corn Seeds

Description:
With a whole bag of these seeds, there is ample opportunity to cultivate the perfect parsnip─and carve it into a horrific visage to ward off island spirits, should the mood strike.

[Growth Period: Two days]
Name: Island Parsnip Seeds

Description:
Rumor has it that these seeds grow into ravishingly redolent radishes. Rumor also has a startlingly suggestive way with words.

[Growth Period: Two days]
Name: Island Radish Seeds

Description: A popoto a day keeps the Lalafells away...or was it the opposite?
Name: Island Popoto

Description: Crisp and crunchy cabbage cultivated in the Cieldalaes.
Name: Island Cabbage

Description: A verifiably nonlethal berry found in the Cieldalaes.
Name: Isleberry

Description: Son of a pump, perhaps.
Name: Island Pumpkin

Description: Like its inland cousins, this round onion bulb does not take kindly to knives.
Name: Island Onion

Description: A ripe tomato cultivated in the Cieldalaes. Goes well with onions, should one be willing to risk it.
Name: Island Tomato

Description: As predicted...wheat.
Name: Island Wheat

Description: Always listening.
Name: Island Corn

Description: A perfect parsnip cultivated in an island paradise.
Name: Island Parsnip

Description: A robust radish ready to add a spicy kick to what will inevitably be dubbed “island salad.”
Name: Island Radish

Description: A basket of wool sheared from a sheep that really, really needed the trim.
Name: Sanctuary Fleece

Description: A stray claw shed by an animal in the sanctuary pasture.
Name: Sanctuary Claw

Description: Clumps of fur shed by an animal in the sanctuary pasture.
Name: Sanctuary Fur

Description: A white feather shed by a cloudkin in the sanctuary pasture.
Name: Sanctuary Feather

Description: An egg laid by an animal in the sanctuary pasture.
Name: Sanctuary Egg

Description: A stray carapace shed by an animal in the sanctuary pasture.
Name: Sanctuary Carapace

Description: A stray fang removed from an animal in the sanctuary pasture during routine dental care.
Name: Sanctuary Fang

Description: A stray horn shed by an animal in the sanctuary pasture.
Name: Sanctuary Horn

Description: This unlabeled liquid was freshly milked from a beast in the sanctuary pasture. Which one, who can recall?
Name: Sanctuary Milk

Description:
Scrumptious bite-sized fruit pieces prepared as feed for animals in the sanctuary pasture. Satisfactorily filling, a serving of this treat will brighten any hungry critter's mood.

[Improves mood up to: Content]
Name: Island Sweetfeed

Description:
A healthy assortment of vegetables prepared as feed for animals in the sanctuary pasture. Pleasantly filling, a serving of this tasty fodder will have animals jumping for joy.

[Improves mood up to: Chipper]
Name: Island Greenfeed

Description:
This assortment of vegetables is the veritable cream of the crop, prepared as feed for animals in the sanctuary pasture. Perfectly filling, a serving of this exquisite fodder will leave animals feeling jubilant and revitalized.

[Improves mood up to: Gleeful]
Name: Premium Island Greenfeed

Description:
A crude net made by attaching elastic vines to a branch of fleeting sturdiness. Breaks after a single use due to its frail construction.

[Can be used to catch small animals.]
Name: Makeshift Net

Description:
A rudimentary restraint made by attaching metallic weights to each end of a hempen rope. Breaks after a single use due to its frail construction.

[Can be used to catch average-sized animals.]
Name: Makeshift Restraint

Description:
A sleep-inducing pellet made by grinding an assortment of raw materials into a fine powder, before kneading them into a ball with bits of clay. A single pellet may only be used once.

[Can be used to catch large animals.]
Name: Makeshift Soporific

Description:
This fermented cabbage dish has a distinctive sour flavor, and can be preserved for however long one is willing to tempt fate.

Category: Preserved Food
Required Time: 4 hours
Name: Isleworks Sauerkraut

Description:
Despite being a homemade recipe cobbled together with ingredients scrounged up in the Cieldalaes, this savory stone oven-baked pumpkin dish is a dainty delight.

Category: Foodstuffs
Required Time: 4 hours
Name: Isleworks Baked Pumpkin

Description:
A simple hempen tunic woven in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Attire/Textiles
Required Time: 6 hours
Name: Isleworks Tunic

Description:
A knife made from a sanctuary claw. Can cut a mean vegetable, and nice ones too.

Category: Sundries/Creature Creations
Required Time: 4 hours
Name: Isleworks Culinary Knife

Description:
A basic brush assembled in the sanctuary workshop, fashioned from wood. 

Category: Sundries/Woodworks
Required Time: 4 hours
Name: Isleworks Brush

Description:
Boiled using fresh water from a sanctuary spring. Add a sprinkle of salt and a pinch of pepper for peak delectability.

Category: Foodstuffs/Creature Creations
Required Time: 4 hours
Name: Isleworks Boiled Egg

Description:
A pugilist's weapon made from a sanctuary carapace.

Category: Arms/Creature Creations
Required Time: 6 hours
Name: Isleworks Hora

Description:
A pair of earrings fashioned from a sanctuary fang.

Category: Accessories/Creature Creations
Required Time: 4 hours
Name: Isleworks Earrings

Description:
A slab of butter churned from sanctuary milk.

Category: Ingredients/Creature Creations
Required Time: 4 hours
Name: Isleworks Butter

Description:
A wooden chair assembled in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Furnishings/Woodworks
Required Time: 6 hours
Name: Isleworks Wooden Chair

Description:
A simple restorative concoction made in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Concoctions
Required Time: 4 hours
Name: Isleworks Potion

Description:
A simple wooden necklace made in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Accessories/Woodworks
Required Time: 4 hours
Name: Isleworks Necklace

Description:
A fresh island clam grilled over an open flame until its shell has opened, then seasoned with a simple mixture of rock salt and butter.

Category: Foodstuffs/Marine Merchandise
Required Time: 4 hours
Name: Isleworks Grilled Clam

Description:
A sanguine ring made of coral, constructed in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Accessories/Marine Merchandise
Required Time: 6 hours
Name: Isleworks Coral Ring

Description:
A copper helm constructed in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Attire/Metalworks
Required Time: 6 hours
Name: Isleworks Barbut
